parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater fan can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: the heater fan makes a burning smell
the heater fan produces excessive noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the outside mirror can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the outside mirror is difficult to adjust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake lining can cause reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and potentially lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when applying the brakes
brake warning lights or messages on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch can cause the headlights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights do not turn on
the headlights are dim or flickering
the headlight switch is hot to the touch
there is a burning smell or smoke coming from the headlight switch.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Radiator failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to damage to the engine, coolant leaks, and potentially causing a loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The partial breakage of the fan blade can cause damage to surrounding components, such as the oil fill line and compressor wire, leading to compressor failure and potential engine damage.
